COURSES.name: Introduction to Aerospace Engineering
COURSES.description: Overview of aerospace engineering. Standard atmosphere, basic aerodynamics, airplane performance, stability and control, propulsion, and space flight.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: PHY 2048 or PHY 2060, with minimum grade of C.

COURSES.name: Aerodynamics
COURSES.description: Incompressible aerodynamics, integral and differential governing equations, potential flow, boundary layers, airfoils, wings, numerical techniques.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: EAS 2011 or EAS 3020C or EGN 3353C and COP 2271, EML 3100, MAC 2313 and MAP 2302 with minimum grades of C.

COURSES.name: Compressible Flow
COURSES.description: One-dimensional and quasi one-dimensional compressible fluid flows. Includes mach waves, normal shocks, oblique shocks, Prandtl-Meyer expansions, isentropic flow with area change, Fanno flow and Rayleigh flow.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: EAS 4101 or EGN 3353C

COURSES.name: Aerospace Structures
COURSES.description: Review of plane states of stress and strain. Includes analysis of thin-walled beams with open and closed section, unsymmetrical bending of wing sections, torsion of skin-stringer and multi-cell sections, flexural shear in open and closed sections, Shear Center and failure criteria. Also includes introduction to composite materials and demonstration of behavior of some simple structural elements.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: EGM 3520.

COURSES.name: Stability and Control of Aircraft
COURSES.description: Static stability and control, equations of motion, stability derivatives, stability of longitudinal and lateral motion of aircraft.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: EAS 4101 and EML 4312.

COURSES.name: Aerospace Design 1
COURSES.description: Applications of the principles of analysis and design to aerospace vehicles. Emphasizes astronautics.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: EAS 4510 and EML 4312.

COURSES.name: Aerospace Sciences Lab and Design
COURSES.description: Experimental investigations of aerospace engineering systems. Wind tunnel testing. Design project with experimental validation.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: EAS 4101 and EML 3301C.

COURSES.name: Individual Study in Aerospace Engineering
COURSES.description: Selected problems or projects in the student's major field of engineering study.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: department chair recommendation.

COURSES.name: Integrated Product and Process Design 1
COURSES.description: The first of a two-course sequence in which multidisciplinary teams of engineering and business students partner with industry sponsors to design and build authentic products and processes-on time and within budget. Working closely with industry liaison engineers and a faculty coach, students gain practical experience in teamwork and communication, problem solving and engineering design, and develop leadership, management and people skills.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: EAS 4101, EGM 3520 and EML 3301C.

COURSES.name: Special Topics in Aerospace Engineering
COURSES.description: Special topics in aerospace engineering.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: instructor permission.

COURSES.name: Co-op Work Experience
COURSES.description: Practical engineering work under industrial supervision, as set forth in the college regulations. (S-U)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: 2EG classification.

COURSES.name: Engineering Mechanics: Statics
COURSES.description: Reduction of force systems, equilibrium of particles and rigid bodies, vector methods and their application to structures and mechanisms.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: PHY 2048; Coreq: MAC 2313.

COURSES.name: Introduction to Numerical Methods of Engineering Analysis
COURSES.description: Methods for numerical solution of mathematical problems with emphasis on engineering applications using MATLAB. Includes roots, optimization, linear algebraic equations, matrices, curve fitting, differentiation, integration and ordinary differential equations.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: MAC 2313 and COP 2271; Coreq: MAP2302.

COURSES.name: Engineering Mechanics: Dynamics
COURSES.description: Continues the dynamics sequence begun in EGM 3400 plus extended coverage of three-dimensional rigid-body dynamics and orbital motion.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: EGM 2511 or EGM 2500, and MAC 2313.

COURSES.name: Mechanics of Materials
COURSES.description: Stress and strain at a point, stress-strain-temperature relations and mechanical properties of materials. Systems subject to axial load, torsion and bending. Design concepts, indeterminate structures and applications.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: EGM 2511 (not EGM 2500) and MAC 2313.

COURSES.name: Bio-Solid Mechanics
COURSES.description: Introduction to solid and fluid mechanics of biological systems. Includes rheological behavior of materials subjected to static and dynamic loading, the mechanics of cardiovascular, pulmonary and renal systems, and the mathematical models and analytical techniques used in biosciences.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: EGM 3520.

COURSES.name: Fluid Mechanics
COURSES.description: Statics and dynamics of incompressible fluids. Application to viscous and inviscid flows. Dimensional analysis. Compressible flow.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: MAC 2313, EGM 2511 and EML 3100, or EML 3007.

COURSES.name: Engineering Directed Independent Research
COURSES.description: Provides firsthand, supervised research with a faculty advisor or postdoctoral or graduate student mentor. Projects may involve inquiry, design, investigation, scholarship, discovery or application. (S-U)

COURSES.name: Computer Aided Graphics and Design
COURSES.description: Sketching, descriptive geometry, computer graphics, computer aided drafting and design projects.

COURSES.name: Design and Manufacturing Laboratory
COURSES.description: Study and application of design, problem formulation, conceptual design, prototype development. Study of common manufacturing processes.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 2; Prereq: EML 2023, ENC 3246 and EG-ME or EG-ASE major.

COURSES.name: Department and Professional Orientation
COURSES.description: Principles of mechanical and aerospace engineering practice, professional standards, engineering ethics.

COURSES.name: Mechanical Engineering Design 1
COURSES.description: Design process, kinematics, gear trains and standard mechanical components.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: COP 2271, EML2322L and EGM 3520 with minimum grade of C.

COURSES.name: Thermodynamics
COURSES.description: Application of the first and second laws of thermodynamics to closed and open systems and to cyclic heat engines. Includes the development of procedures for calculating the properties of multiphase and singlephase pure substances.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: CHM 2045, MAC 2313 and PHY 2048.

COURSES.name: Mechanics of Materials Laboratory
COURSES.description: Experimental characterization of the mechanical properties of engineering materials, precision instruments, computer-based data acquisition, statistical uncertainty analysis, preparation of engineering reports. (WR)
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: EGM 3520, EGM 3344, and ENC 2210 or ENC 3254.

COURSES.name: Heat Transfer
COURSES.description: Steady state and transient analysis of conduction and radiation heat transfer in stationary media. Also discusses heat transfer in fluid systems, including forced and free convection.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: MAP 2302 with minimum grade of C and EAS 4101 or EGN 3353C.

COURSES.name: Thermo-Heat Transfer Design and Laboratory
COURSES.description: Thermodynamics and heat transfer integrated with design and laboratory, including heat exchange design, phase-change heat transfer, thermodynamics of mixtures, psychometry, mass transfer and sensible heat recovery.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: EML 3100, EML 3301C and EML 4140.

COURSES.name: Vibrations
COURSES.description: Single and multiple degree of freedom systems, including application to mechanical systems with problems employing computer techniques.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: EGM 3344, EGM 3401, EGM 3520 and MAP 2302 with minimum grades of C.

COURSES.name: Control of Mechanical Engineering Systems
COURSES.description: Theory, analysis and design of control systems, including mechanical, electromechanical, hydraulic, pneumatic and thermal components and systems.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: EGM 3401, EGM 3344 and MAP 2302 with minimum grades of C.

COURSES.name: Dynamics and Controls System Design Laboratory
COURSES.description: Experiments on dynamic systems in mechanical and aerospace engineering and design of relevant control systems.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: EML 3301C and EML 4312.

COURSES.name: Manufacturing Engineering
COURSES.description: Descriptive and analytical treatment of manufacturing processes and production equipment  automation  computer control and integrated systems. Applications of mechanics stress analysis  vibrations  controls  heat transfer. Discrete time simulation.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: EMA 3010, EML 2322L, and EGM 3520 with minimum grade of C.

COURSES.name: Mechanical Engineering Design 2
COURSES.description: Integrated design and presentation of a mechanical system.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: EGN 3353C, EML 2322L, EML 3005 and EGM 3401 with minimum grade of C; Coreq: EML 4321 and EML 4507.

COURSES.name: Mechanical Engineering Design 3
COURSES.description: Design and realization of a mechanical engineering system, component, or process subject to appropriate standards and constraints. Team Project.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: EML 4501; Coreq: EML 4321.

COURSES.name: Finite Element Analysis and Design
COURSES.description: Stress-strain analysis and design of machine elements and finite element analysis.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 3; Prereq: EGM 3344, EGM 3520 and MAP 2302 with minimum grades of C.
